## SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Prologue – Companions Kneel for Prayer.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/18-sm-prologue-prayer.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE
%SPACE
KS: We will now resume our labors. Companion Captain of
   the Guard, form a procession and lead us to the Secret
   Vault.

CG: Craftsmen, form a procession on the North, facing East.

Note: Procession is formed. K._S. places himself at the head
   and C._G. places himself at the rear. (See Fig. 19)

CG: Forward, March!

Note: After a moment, C._C. continues to speak, as the
   procession moves east, then south, then west, then
   north, and waits to exit at the preparation room
   door:

CC: What do I hear? Is the craft engaged in some secret
   work? Let us return to the Inner Gate.

Note: C._C. closes the Sentinel's door, and conducts the
   candidate(s) back from the Sentinel's room to the
   Preparation Room. (See Fig. 20)
%PAGE figure
Figure 19.

## SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Prologue – Forming a Procession.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/19-sm-prologue-procession.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE figure
Figure 20.

SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Prologue – Procession Begins to March.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/20-sm-prologue-march.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE
%SPACE
CC: (_Attempt to open door but feigns it being locked._)
   The gate is locked. We will make an alarm. ●●●
   (_Pause._) No answer. ●●● (_Pause._) We will make one
   more attempt. ●●●

Note: Companions in the procession stamp their feet.

CC: I hear footsteps, stand back!

Note: C._C. gestures for candidate(s) to step back.  K._S.
   opens the door without returning the alarm. The
   procession advances forward so that K._S. and the
   first few Companions in the procession are through
   the door, and then halts. (See Fig. 21)

KS: Zabud, my friend! Why do you linger without the Inner
   Gate at such a late hour?
CC: (_Dropping to his knee, if possible, with arms
  outstretched._) Illustrious King Solomon! Of late I find
  a secret work going on, of which I have not been
  informed, and I fear I have lost your Majesty's favor.
KS: Be content, friend Zabud. (_Offers hand to Zabud_)
   Arise! The time will come when a door shall be opened
   for your reception. Good night.

Note: K._S. and procession continue forward. After C._G.
   passes out of the room, he closes the door firmly and
   continues past the candidate(s). The procession
   proceeds into the Sentinel's room and from thence
   back into the Council Room, leaving the door wide
   open.

%PAGE figure
Figure 21.

