## SELECT MASTER DEGREE – FIRST SECTION | Nine Arches – As seen from the West.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/22-sm-nine-arches.png" 29
%SPACE
The distance should be about 15 feet from the First to the
Ninth Arch, where a white veil keeps the candidate(s) from seeing
the Substitute Ark and its future contents until the appropriate time.
The incomplete arches may be made of wood, without
back or side panels so as to be stackable; or made of painted
canvas mounted on frames which are hinged together for folding.
%PAGE
%SPACE
## ZABUD ATTEMPTS TO VISIT KING SOLOMON

.rubric The Council Room should now be made to fully represent the
  Secret Vault with its Nine Aches. Eight of these arches are in
  the process of construction, and the Ninth Arch is completed.
  (See Fig. 22) Optionally, as the arrangements for the Secret
  Vault are finalized, [[em]]"Ahishar's Soliloquy"[[/em]] may be performed.
 
.rubric The East end of the room represents the crypt within the Ninth
  Arch, and must be large enough for candidate(s) and C._C. to
  witness the deposit. One or more pedestals on or in front of the
  dais should house the Substitute Ark and the articles for the
  Deposit. {{endnote-ref articles-for-deposit}} Each Arch should be wide enough for
  up to three candidates and C._C. to stand side by side, and there
  should be about one step from each arch to the next. The West
  end of the room represents the passage leading to the First
  Arch, and should be left as large as possible. The room should
  be moderately lit, and one or more spot-lights shining down
  into the partially constructed arches and into the (veiled) inner
  recess of the Ninth Arch may be used to good effect.

.rubric The Altar is placed in the Southwest, with a gavel near or upon
  it (but not upon the Great Lights) for use by K._S.

Note: The Steward, Ahishar, should lay down on the floor
   just within the Council Room and feign sleep, so that
   anyone entering the room is obliged to step over
   his body. C._C. and Candidate(s) remain in the
   preparation room until all have passed through.
   (See Fig. 23) The Sentinel's Room now represents |
   King Solomon's Most Retired Apartment.

CC: A number of days later, just when Zabud had completed
   his labor, he was approached by an Entered Apprentice
   with a particularly difficult question regarding the plans
   which he had been commissioned to complete before the
   next Sabbath. After deliberating until a late hour, having
   reached no consensus, and deeming this important
   business, Zabud resolved to seek out King Solomon in
   his most retired apartment, and take the matter before
   him, as he had often done before.

%PAGE figure
Figure 23.

## SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Setup for Discovery.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/23-sm-setup-for-discovery.png" 26
%SPACE
Members of Procession take their Places in the Secret Vault.
%PAGE figure
Figure 24.

SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Zabud Discovers the Secret Vault.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/24-sm-zabud-discovers-secret-vault.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE
%SPACE
Note: C._C. conducts candidate(s) from the preparation
   room to the threshold of the Sentinel's room and just
   before entering it says:

CC: We are entering King Solomon's most retired apartment
   now, (_stepping into Sentinel's room_) but, where is he?
   (_Points to the open door of the Council Room._) Here
   is an open door! Perhaps this is the one to which King
   Solomon referred?

## RECEPTION OF CANDIDATE(S)

Note: C._C. chooses one candidate to more particularly
   represent Zabud, telling him that if anyone asks who
   he is he must say: "A zealous brother, wishing to
   participate in your labors." C._C. and candidate(s)
   enter the Sentinel's door without Alarm, each
   following direction of C._C., stepping deliberately
   over the sleeping body of Ahishar. (See Fig. 24)

CG: Who comes here?
Cand: A zealous brother, wishing to participate in your labors.
   (_Prompted by C._C._)
CG: Give me the pass, sign, and token of your entrance.
Cand: I cannot.
CG: Intruder! ... Guards, come quickly!

Note: Craftsmen with drawn swords surround the
   candidate. The Three Grand Masters pass hurriedly
   through the veil from the Ninth Arch to the First.

KS: Companion Captain of the Guard, what is the cause of
   this confusion?
CG: An intruder has entered our Secret Vault.
KS: Then put him to death at once.

Note: One of the Guards raises sword as if to strike Zabud,
   but the Captain of the Guard, recognizing the
   prisoner, parries the blow, steps between the guard
   and Zabud and says:
%PAGE
CG: Hold! Illustrious King Solomon, are you aware upon
   whom you are about to execute this awful sentence?
   This is none other than your particular friend, Zabud.
KS: Zabud!? Is it possible? Companion Captain of the
   Guard, bind him fast and bring him forth when called
   for, or your life shall answer for his escape.

Note: C._G. places Zabud in shackles, and takes him along
   with C._C. to the northwest corner. (See Fig. 25)

KS: (To H._K._T. and H._A.) Illustrious Companions, let us
   return to the Ninth Arch for consultation.

Note: K._S., H._K._T. and H._A. go East through the Nine
   Arches without ceremony, passing behind the veil.

KS: Companions, you are aware that Zabud has long been
   my particular friend and favorite. If it were possible, I
   should be glad to pardon him. My worthy Companion of
   Tyre, what is your opinion?
HKT: Illustrious King Solomon, our obligations are such that
   but twenty-seven can be admitted. Our number is full.
   How then can he be pardoned?
KS: My worthy Companion Hiram Abiff, what do you say?
HA: Illustrious King Solomon, it would seem that curiosity
   and disobedience prompted him to enter; he should
   therefore suffer the penalty.
KS: It seems indeed impossible to save him. Let us return to
   the First Arch and announce our decision.

Note: K._S., H._K._T. and H._A. pass through the veil and
   return to the First Arch.

KS: Bring forth the prisoner. (_See Fig. 26_)
KS: My unfortunate friend Zabud, your curiosity and
   disobedience has cost you your life. I have consulted
   with my colleagues and find them inexorable. The
   nature of our obligation is such that I cannot pardon
   you. You must therefore prepare for death.

Note: C._C. and Zabud fall to their knees (if practicable.)
%PAGE figure
Figure 25.

SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Intrusion – The Prisoner is Bound.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/25-sm-intrusion.png" 26
%SPACE
When C._G. takes candidates to the northwest, C._C. accompanies
him. King Solomon's Guard causes the remaining candidates to
stand with him along the west side of the room.
%PAGE figure
Figure 26.

SELECT MASTER DEGREE | Intrusion – The Prisoner is Brought Forth.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/26-sm-brought-forth.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE
CC: (_representing Zabud_) Illustrious King Solomon, I pray
   that your Majesty might remember my great and sincere
   attachment to your sacred person, your service, and your
   secrets. Of late, finding a secret work going on with
   which I was not made acquainted, I feared that I had lost
   your Majesty's favor and inquired of you, as you
   undoubtedly recall. I made known my fears, after which
   you directed me to remain content, saying that a door
   would soon be opened for my reception. This assurance
   satisfied me and I waited in patience. This evening,
   having important business to bring before your Majesty,
   I sought you as usual at your private apartment, but |
   upon arriving found a door open. I took it for granted
   that it had been left open for my reception, and entered.
   But, I beg your Majesty to believe that it was not
   curiosity or disobedience that led me hither, but
   fervency and zeal in your Majesty's service.
HKT: Illustrious King Solomon, if this be true, Zabud is not
   guilty of the charge alleged against him. His offense was
   owing to an unguarded expression of your own. He
   ought to be pardoned and admitted one of our Select
   Masters.
KS: My worthy Companion of Tyre, how can that be? Is our
   number not already full?

Note: Hiram Abiff sees Ahishar sleeping at his post.

HA: `Tis true, Illustrious King Solomon, our number is
   already full, but Ahishar the guard, is no longer worthy
   of our confidence. He is sleeping at his post. Let him be
   dismissed and executed and Zabud appointed to the
   work.
KS: My worthy Companion, I thank you for this advice. It
   shall be done. Companion Captain of the Guard, let
   Ahishar be put to death instantly.
CG: Ahishar! Ahishar! Awake and arise. Thou art condemned <|
   to die.
Ahishar: Mercy! Mercy! Is there no mercy?
CG: None for you—it has been extended to another.

Note: Ahishar is taken out by C._G. and guards. C._G.
   returns and reports:
%PAGE
%SPACE
CG: Illustrious King Solomon, your order has been obeyed.

KS: Zabud, my companion, you have labored zealously for
  many years. You have been initiated, passed and raised
  to the Sublime Degree of Master Mason, advanced to
  the Degree of Mark Master Mason, inducted into the
  Oriental Chair as a Past Master, received and
  acknowledged a Most Excellent Master, exalted to the
  Most Sublime and August Degree of the Holy Royal
  Arch, and introduced to the Sanctum Sanctorum as a
  Royal Master. Now, by our decision, you have been
  chosen to assist in the building of the Secret Vault as a
  Select Master, but first you must take a solemn
  obligation to keep the secrets appertaining to this
  engagement. This obligation can never be repudiated or
  laid aside. It contains nothing which can conflict with
  your duty to God, your country, your neighbor, or
  yourself. Companion(s) A, B, C, and D—with this
  assurance on my part as Master of the Council, are you
  willing to take this obligation as all Select Masters have
  done before?
Cand: I am.
KS: (_Offering hand._) Then, arise. Companion Captain of
   the Guard, free our companion from his shackles and
   teach him how to approach the east as a Select Master.
%PAGE figure
Figure 27.

