## THE OBLIGATION

KS: Say I, pronounce your name in full, and repeat after me: ||
   O m o f w - i t~ p> o A G - t> I> C o S+ M>, e< t h - d< |
   t o 3 A+ G M, d h - h m+ s - s p> - s t+ I w a h, f c - n r a |
   o t~ s‘ a>, p>, o p> o t~ m o A+ F a@ t t> d t a o i t~ w, |
   e i+ b t a C S+ M o w t~ b o a j+ - r c< C o S+ M>, - n u |
   h o t u a s+ t, d e, o l i, I s h f h o t a j e t r t a I a. <|
   I f p> - s that I will answer all due signs and obey all |
   regular summonses coming from a Council of Select
   Masters or given to me by a Companion of this degree,
   if within my power to do so. ||
   Furthermore, I will stand to and abide by all the laws,
   rules, and regulations of the Council of Select Masters
   of which I am a member, and will maintain and support
   the constitution, laws, and edicts of the Grand Council
   under whose jurisdiction my Council works, so far as
   they shall come to my knowledge. ||
   Furthermore, I will help aid and assist all distressed
   worthy Companion Select Masters, their widows and
   orphans, wheresoever dispersed, so far as their needs
   require and my circumstances permit. ||
   Furthermore, I will not cheat, wrong, or defraud a
   Council of Select Masters, or a Companion of this
   Degree, out of the value of anything knowingly. ||
   Furthermore, I will not be present at or assist with the
   conferring of this degree upon any person unless he
   shall have regularly received all the preceding degrees
   from Entered Apprentice Mason to Royal Master,
   inclusive, and only then in a just and regularly
   constituted Council of Select Masters. ||
   Furthermore, I will not penetrate the Ninth Arch without
   permission of the Illustrious Master. ||
   A t> I m+ s - s p> - s w a f< - f r t k - p t~ s, w t~ l e, m
   r, o s e, b m u n l a p t t+ o h@ m e> p <o+, m h> c <o,
   (_C._G., assisted by C._C., demonstrates signs of e> p<
   o+ - h> c< off only, then repositions the candidate's
   hands._) m b‘ q< - t among t~ r, s I i t l k v+ t>, m s o‘.
   S h m G, - k m s. {{endnote-ref sm-signs-obligation}}
KS: D y h>, - i t o y s i t> s o‘, k> t HB o b y.

