## SELECT MASTER DEGREE – FIRST SECTION | Instruction Given After the Obligation
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/29-sm-instruction.png" 26
%SPACE
%PAGE
%SPACE
Note: Grand Masters return to the East and K._S. seats the
   Council with ●. C._C. conducts candidate(s) to form
   a line to the west of the First Arch, running from
   north to south, with C._C. being on the north end of
   the line.  C._G. goes to the south side, within the First
   Arch and faces west.

## INSTRUCTION

Note: All three Grand Masters come down together |
   (See Fig. 29) and demonstrate the signs as King
   Solomon explains:

KS: You observe me as Master of the Council, assisted by
   Hiram King of Tyre and Hiram Abiff, approaching you
   from the east by the step (_all three demonstrate
   together_), under the due-guard and penal signs of a
   Select Master. (_all three give due-guard and signs of
   e> p< o+ - h> c< off_) Select Masters a o s w t l f, b t h o
   t r t t h o t l, f 2 s> o a e △.  This is the due-guard
   (_all three demonstrate_) and first penal-sign (_p o+ e>_)
   of a S._M., and this (_c o h>_) is the second penal sign of a
   S._M.  Taken together, they allude to the first portion of
   the penalty of the obligation, that of having your e> p<
   o+ - y h> c< o. Ever remember upon entering or retiring
   from a Council of Select Masters to advance to the altar,
   and salute the I._M. w t> d-g< - t^ p s> (_K. S. alone
   demonstrates again; K._S. should step forward
   towards the candidate(s), but should not move to the
   altar for this demonstration_). The Grand Hailing Sign,
   or Sign of Distress is made by drawing the edge o t~ r+ |
   h f t~ l s t t~ r+ hip, - t~ l h f t~ r+ s t t~ l+ hip, then throwing <|
   t~ h> t t~ l+. (_demonstrates._) It alludes to the second
   portion of the penalty, that of having your b q< - t a t~
   rubbish. We will now invest you with the Pass, Sign,
   and Token of Entrance to the Secret Vault, by which you
   will be enabled to pass the F+ E+ A>, and in which you
   were deficient when challenged by the Captain of the
   Guard. On being asked, "W c h?" you reply, "Giblim."
   The Guard then says, "Advance - g t s‘ - t o y e>."  You
   answer with this (_Demonstrate, with the t - last 2 f> o
   t~ r+ h‘ closed in the palm thereof, place t~ f+ 2 f>
   diagonally across t~ m. Pause, then drop the sign._),
   the Sign of Silence. He responds with this
   (_Demonstrate, r+ h< on t~ l+ b‘. Pause, then drop the
   sign._), the Sign of Secrecy. Finally, both give this final
   token (_Demonstrate, s‘ of S> as above, - left h< o t~
   e>_), the Sign of Silence and Darkness.  With this pass,
   sign, and token, you will be enabled to pass the F+ E+
   A>.

   These signs allude to the fact that you should always
   keep the whole world in silence and darkness with
   respect to the mysteries of the Secret Vault. Labor well,
   Zabud, and henceforth be voluntarily dumb and blind to
   all that you have seen and heard, or that you may yet
   see or hear in the Ninth Arch, for we now invest you
   with the Grip and Word of a Select Master. ||
   (_Demonstrates; each Grand Master may take a |
   different candidate for this—_) This is the grip. (_With
   t~ l h< take t~ r+ lapel, inserting f+ 2 f> under t~
   lapel, - gr@ with t~ t on top._) The name of the grip is
   "Ish Sodi" which signifies "Man of my Choice" or
   "Select Man."

Note: Each candidate must receive the grip and word
   before proceeding. The Three Grand Masters may
   move about the candidates to do so.

KS: Zabud, being obligated and instructed, you are now
   qualified to penetrate the Ninth Arch.

Note: The Three Grand Masters face East (each turning
   clockwise) and return to the Ninth Arch. After they
   pass into the arches, C._G. steps out into the middle
   of the First Arch, facing West. (See Fig. 30)

%PAGE figure
Figure 30.

SELECT MASTER DEGREE – FIRST SECTION | Grand Masters Return to the Ninth Arch.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/30-sm-return-ninth-arch.png" 26
%SPACE
After C._G. has stepped to the middle of the First Arch and the
Three Grand Masters have entered the Ninth Arch as illustrated,
they will take their places within the Secret Vault and the Second
Section of the Degree will begin immediately.

K._S. raps the gavel. C._C. and candidate(s) begin to advance (not
illustrated) but C._G. steps forward to block them and demands
"Who comes here?" After answering his questions, they pass
through the first Eight Arches as directed by C._C. where they will
request to penetrate the Ninth Arch.

%END-PAGE
